  "Group 18, because noble gases are unreactive and exist as gases": "",
  "Group 2, because alkaline earth metals do not react with anything": "",
  "An unreactive gas at room temperature describes a noble gas (Group 18). Noble gases have full outer electron shells, making them extremely stable and unreactive.": "",
  "Oxygen (Group 16) has 6 valence electrons. A student says oxygen needs to gain 2 electrons to become stable. Is this correct, and why?": "",
  "No, oxygen needs to lose 6 electrons to become stable in reactions": "",
